description:
Carlos is passionate about the teaching case method. He is co-author of more than 25 of them in the areas of finance, strategy, operations, and sustainability. Some of them have been included in the case databases of prestigious business schools such as Harvard, Michigan, and IESE.

He has oriented his research towards the impact of social, environmental, and corporate governance (ESG) information on financial markets. He has also carried out studies on entrepreneurial financing in contexts with institutional voids.

His research has been presented at prestigious conferences such as the Alliance for Research on Corporate Sustainability (MIT, USA) doctoral colloquium, the specialized conference “From Start-up to Scale-up” of the Academy of Management (University of Tel-Aviv, Israel ), the Third Conference on Entrepreneurial Finance (Politecnico di Milano, Italy) and the Annual Congress of the European Accounting Association (Valencia, Spain).

Carlos is the co-author of five papers in peer-reviewed scientific journals and two book chapters (published by Edward Elgar and World Scientific Publishing). His research has been cited by the International Integrated Reporting Council in white papers for institutional investors. Additionally, he has been an occasional reviewer for various academic journals.

Sobresale en la construcción de marcas con propósito, diseño y descubrimiento de consumer insights, planning y storytelling de marcas, estrategia digital, diseño de research y consulting. Especialista en Hispanic and Latino markets.

Amplia experiencia como creativa y planner en diversas agencias reconocidas de la región. Trabajando para marcas líderes locales y regionales con las que ha ganado 5 Effies, además de otros premios creativos locales y centroamericanos.

Su constante interés por fortalecer el impacto social de las marcas la ha llevado a ser parte y dirigir esfuerzos de trascendencia en temas como malnutrición infantil, abuso contra la mujer y la niñez, prevención de violencia intrafamiliar entre otros temas. Lo que la lleva a fundar la innovadora iniciativa Social Impact Planning que replantean el RSE con una mirada más estratégica y creativa, alineada a la construcción de marcas con propósito. Así también ha formado parte de equipos de asesoría en estrategia de comunicación para partidos políticos y proyectos ciudadanos emergentes.

Es conferencista activa, creadora de talleres, charlas y seminarios a nivel nacional e internacional, en diversas plataformas y universidades. Es así como mantiene viva su pasión por enseñar y formar talento estratégico.

Lideró el departamento más grande de planning integrado del país, además de ser nombrada Black Belt en herramientas estratégicas de la red global y dirigir el área de Consulting en El Salvador y proyectos para CA.

Actiz para cine y televisión.

description:
Nabyl Charania is most passionate about leaving a positive, generational, world-changing legacy. He chases this higher aspiration through a personal Massive Transformative Purpose (MTP) he has set and challenged himself to achieve in his lifetime: Create incorruptible prosperity and abundant ecosystems for all across the universe.

Nabyl draws inspiration for his MTP from the ethical framework of the Aga Khan Development Network (AKDN) and the mission of the XPRIZE Foundation. As a legacy donor, he supports the AKDN’s fundamental objective to improve the quality of human life through a variety of agencies working in the fields of economic development, education, healthcare, and cultural enrichment. As a member of the XPRIZE Vision Circle, Nabyl joins Larry Page, Sergey Brin, Ratan Tata, and other global business leaders to contribute thought leadership and funds for XPRIZE’s large-scale global incentive competitions that crowdsource solutions to the world’s grand challenges. Nabyl is also fascinated by space, and is excited to pursue space travel and other space projects that line up with his MTP.

Nabyl is a serial entrepreneur with multiple exits, and has seeded several successful companies as well as crypto funds with outstanding returns. He founded Rokk3r, one of the first company builders globally that over the years has evolved into a strategic holding company focussed on exponential technology companies. He is Co-Founder, Fund Sponsor and Curator at Meta4 Capital, where he combines his entrepreneurial track record with his passions for art, music, culture and of course sneakers.

Nabyl grew up in Kenya’s capital city of Nairobi where seeing his dad tinkering with electronics, and his neighbors and community working together to solve any problem no matter how big or small, are his earliest memories of technology and the power of human potential.
headline: Vision Circle at XPRIZE :: Co-Founder at Meta4Capital :: Chairman at Rokk3r :: Founding Partner Rokk3r Fuel ExO

description:
Hey there! I'm Carlos, a young business professional native from El Salvador. I'm currently pursuing my MBA at Simon Fraser University in Vancouver, Canada. I graduated Summa Cum Laude from John Brown University (Arkansas, USA) in May 2016 with a Bachelor of Arts in International Business, a Bachelor of Science in Marketing and Business Administration, and a minor in Leadership. I was recognized as the Highest-Ranking Graduate from the Soderquist College of Business (2016). I have been a scholarship recipient from: Beedie Family Graduate Scholarship (2020), Peter Legge Graduate Volunteer Leadership Award (2020), Walton International Scholarship Program (2012-2016), U.S. Department of State - Youth Ambassadors (2011), and Programa Oportunidades by Gloria de Kriete Foundation (2009-2011).

Upon graduating from college, I returned to my home country to work as a Marketing Analyst for Amway Central America and was promoted in 2018 to Sales Project Manager in Amway Latin America. I believe we all have a responsibility to leave a better world for the future generations, hence I have always been involved in projects and organizations (such as ENACTUS and the Youth Council for the U.S. Embassy in El Salvador) aligned to my passions - entrepreneurship, small business development, and youth empowerment – as part of my giving back philosophy. I served as the Director of the 2016 Alumni Engagement Innovation Fund winning project for El Salvador, “Jóvenes Pioneros” for five years. An organization born out of a $25K grant by the U.S. Department of State that promotes youth entrepreneurship through an innovative business curriculum designed for high school students. In February 2020, I was recognized as one of twenty “Influential Youth from the Republic of El Salvador” for my volunteering endeavors.

In September 2020, I began my MBA studies online - given mobility restrictions - while I also joined local Salvadoran politics and ran for Congress as one of the youngest candidates for El Salvador's February 28, 2021 elections. Shortly after my participation, I was named National Youth Coordinator for the up-and-coming political party, Nuestro Tiempo on April 2021.

My future plans include advancing my professional career in business, continue contributing to the development of sustainable social impact projects, and continue my involvement in Salvadoran politics.

Feel free to reach out to me at carlose.lopezs94@gmail.com!

description:
Daniel Runde is a Senior Vice President at the Center for Strategic and International Studies and holds the William A. Schreyer Chair in Global Analysis, where he focuses on the role of using soft power to shape the future. A global thought leader, Mr. Runde has advised a number of governments including the United States, Japan, Denmark, Korea as well as the World Bank and the United Nations. He has testified before the U.S. Congress, and the Australian and Canadian parliaments.

In April 2018, Mr. Runde was named the Chair of the Advisory Committee for Voluntary Foreign Assistance, the Federal Advisory Committee that advises the Administrator of the US Agency for International Development and the broader federal government on international development issues.

Prior to coming to CSIS, Mr. Runde held senior roles and led organization change initiatives and built strategic partnerships at the World Bank Group and the US Agency for International Development. Mr. Runde is an Opinions Contributor at Thehill.com. He blogs occasionally at "Elephants in the Room" at ForeignPolicy.com. He writes and speaks extensively on global development issues. He was a member of the World Economic Forum Global Agenda Council for the United States. He currently serves on the board of the International Foundation for Electoral Systems (IFES) and the Ashesi University Foundation board, a Ghanaian university.

He has been featured in Inc Magazine's 30 under 30 and Inc 5000. He is also President of Colabora Holdings, a group of companies based in El Salvador that develops businesses within the sharing economy; Point, the first business center and coworking exclusively for entrepreneurs and LIVE the first co-living facility in El Salvador.
Alfredo is Brand Ambassador for El Salvador as Entrepreneur since 2017, he is also part of the Aspen Global Leadership Network and CALI Fellow.
He has been part of YEC and YPO, additionally Alfredo has been involved in The Chamber of Commerce as part of the board of directors from 2016 to 2019.
Alfredo in President of Fundacion Colabora, the group's non profit whose main goal is to promote entrepreneurship in El Salvador via different programs, including an Angel Investment fund.

Estratega y creativa apasionada por construir marcas capaces de impactar este mundo con más que publicidad. Fundadora del primer Purpose Design Studio de la region: ElWhy. Creadora de la metodología Social Impact Planning y parte del equipo de Ogilvy Consulting para la región. Con más de 15 años de experiencia en diversos rubros y mercados. U.S. citizen and fully bilingual.

Sobresale en la construcción de marcas con propósito, diseño y descubrimiento de consumer insights, planning y storytelling de marcas, estrategia digital, diseño de research y consulting. Especialista en Hispanic and Latino markets.

Amplia experiencia como creativa y planner en diversas agencias reconocidas de la región. Trabajando para marcas líderes locales y regionales con las que ha ganado 5 Effies, además de otros premios creativos locales y centroamericanos.

Su constante interés por fortalecer el impacto social de las marcas la ha llevado a ser parte y dirigir esfuerzos de trascendencia en temas como malnutrición infantil, abuso contra la mujer y la niñez, prevención de violencia intrafamiliar entre otros temas. Lo que la lleva a fundar la innovadora iniciativa Social Impact Planning que replantean el RSE con una mirada más estratégica y creativa, alineada a la construcción de marcas con propósito. Así también ha formado parte de equipos de asesoría en estrategia de comunicación para partidos políticos y proyectos ciudadanos emergentes.

Es conferencista activa, creadora de talleres, charlas y seminarios a nivel nacional e internacional, en diversas plataformas y universidades. Es así como mantiene viva su pasión por enseñar y formar talento estratégico.

Lideró el departamento más grande de planning integrado del país, además de ser nombrada Black Belt en herramientas estratégicas de la red global y dirigir el área de Consulting en El Salvador y proyectos para CA.

Actiz para cine y televisión.

description:
Soy Abogado y Politólogo, especialista en investigación, análisis de entorno y diseño de estrategias para la incidencia en políticas públicas que afectan al sector empresarial en todos los ámbitos, especialmente en el regulatorio.

En 2006 luego de años de ejercicio privado acompañando a muchas gremiales y representando a los empresarios de El Salvador en OIT y en otras instancias internacionales, fundé ASES (Asesoría Especializada), una oficina multidisciplinaria dedicada a los asuntos públicos. Hemos acompañado a algunas de las más grandes empresas nacionales e internacionales en áreas, desde la tecnología, medios, industria y comercio hasta la publicidad y libertad de expresión, a enfrentar amenazas regulatorias que afectan su funcionamiento y por tanto sus negocios.

Con mucha pasión y profesionalismo hemos colaborado a diseñar normativas legales balanceadas para los sectores empresariales y las autoridades. Participamos en las complejas reformas de la Ley de Telecomunicaciones de 2016 junto a los medios privados, diseñamos una moderna ley de Gestión Integral de Residuos y Fomento al Reciclaje, hemos participado en las discusiones que promueven una Ley General de Agua con perspectiva del derecho humano al agua pero también para la producción de alimentos, seguimiento a normativas que afectan a la tecnología y muchísimos otros retos alcanzados con éxito.

Creo que el monitoreo anticipado y metódico de todo el contexto que rodea a la formación de regulaciones (política, comunicacional, social y económica) genera información de calidad que bajo un análisis adecuado genera estrategias oportunas para evitar riesgos regulatorios y políticas públicas dañinas al ejercicio de la libre empresa, pero sobre todo abre las puertas a decisiones más balanceadas que incluyan el interés público y el privado, mediante la discusión técnica y hábil negociación.

¿Y tu industria corre algún riesgo regulatorio? ¿no lo sabes? ¿Alguna prohibición, algún impuesto? Si no lo sabes o si ya lo identificaste, es hora de que hablemos!!! Contactame!!!
headline: Abogado y Politólogo. Especialista en diseño de estrategias para incidencia política. Negociador. Asuntos públicos.

description:
I have dedicated myself to designing brands, packaging, and corporate identity for more than 20 years. I have acquired this experience because I worked creatively in two of the most important Mexican design agencies (Praxis Diseñadores y Foic Lecanda). That is why, I was able to manage design projects for global brands as Danone, Kraft, Grupo Bimbo, Nestle, and Procter & Gamble, among others. In addition to this, I worked as Senior Designer for Landor Mexico where I was in charge of creative projects for Gamesa and Philip Morris.

One of my last positions was as Creative Director in Foic Lecanda until December 2019, a position which lasted for 6 years. In 2020 I joined Interbrand as Design Director, being my current position.

Also, I got a Master’s in Strategic Design and Innovation which is based on an innovation methodology called Design Thinking. This is a user-centered approach whose purpose is to offer solutions to unsatisfied needs or complex problems.

Thanks to the knowledge acquired, I was able to create and launch Brand Grid® and Madi® - brand management tools - for Foic Lecanda.

Finally, I was part of the academic group of the Design Department at Universidad Iberoamericana for more than 10 years, where I shared my knowledge about the creative process and graphic production in the Degree in Graphic Design, and in the Technical Career in Graphic Production.

description:
Soy un estudiante de mercadeo internacional, me considero multidisciplinario, de mente abierta, amable, determinado, comprometido, de rápido aprendizaje, excelente manejo de conflictos, originalidad, honestidad, ambicioso, con alto dominio de la tecnología, muy buen servicio al cliente y excelentes técnicas de negociación.

En mi vida he logrado motivar personas a iniciar su propio negocio, a otros a que se inscriban a la universidad, a organizar tareas de limpieza, a que otros reciban un trato digno.

Mi historia...

Empecé a trabajar desde muy chico (13 años) como mesero en un modesto hotel de playa en La Costa del Sol, para finalizar 2008 emigré a Santa Ana para seguir estudiando mi bachillerato, trabajaba en una zapatería como vendedor; sin embargo, también me encargaba de la facturación y manejo de caja, negociación con proveedores, manejo de pedidos e inventarios.

Trabajé en un call center siempre en Santa Ana siendo colaborador activo de 4 empresas en el transcurso de un poco más de 3 años (Transactel, Telus, Tetel y OneLink) trabajando para Claro Costa Rica y Claro El Salvador. Las funciones principales eran: resolución de quejas por facturación, inconvenientes con hardware, asistencia técnica para el uso efectivo de los productos, servicios o aplicaciones que ofrecía la compañía, manejo de problemas de conectividad, etc.
Fuí asignado como Senior Analyst rápidamente lo que me permitió adquirir habilidades de manejo de personal y reacción inmediata para coordinar con el cliente (Claro) la implementación de planes de contingencia ante fallas masivas de manera urgente y el procesamiento efectivo y oportuno de la Data.
En esa misma empresa también formé parte del Comité de Seguridad Ocupacional en el cual mi rol era la evaluación periódica de zonas de riesgo y presentación de formularios con recomendaciones para el acondicionamiento del espacio de trabajo, en ocasiones se daban charlas a los demás compañeros para garantizar la integridad de todos.

description:
Hola, me puedes llamar Luis Eduardo 🙂

Actualmente trabajo en la industria de las telecomunicaciones, enfocado en regular, optimizar, solucionar problemas y procesos con software.

Mi día a día involucra mantener la disponibilidad de la red al 99% y me gusta mi trabajo porque me exige estar atento. Siento que soy bombero apaga fuegos cuando uno de nuestros sistemas o red se cae 👨🏽‍🚒

Desde el 2019 me llené de pasión por el desarrollo de software. Desde entonces día con día para cada problema que veo me da vueltas la cabeza pensando como se podría solucionar con software.

Aprendí a hacer código de manera autodidacta. Aprendí a no subestimar el valor de la disciplina. El ser disciplinado con mis horas al día de practica y estudio acerca del desarrollo de software, protocolos, linux, networking etc... ha sido para mí como un deporte de alto rendimiento 🏋🏽‍♂️

Me gusta plantear proyectos, llevarlos a papel y lápiz o Notion y ejecutarlos. Cuando me encuentro con un problema me gusta dividirlo en partes pequeñas e ir solucionando de a uno en uno hasta resolver todo. Me gusta documentar todo y tomar nota de cosas importantes que me puedan servir a futuro, y ¿adivina...? también en Notion.

Mis mejores herramientas son: Notion, VS code, Git, Github, Hyper, Discord y en resumen me gusta resolver problemas con software basandome en documentacipon oficial, estándares y papers científicos.

¿Quieres saber mas? 👉 www.luissotoj.com

Entre las experiencias claves puedo destacar:
-Proyectos de implementación de sistemas operativos y software IT, así como migraciones de datos.
-Proyectos de logística enfocados a la recepción, almacenamiento, despacho y reabastecimiento de inventario.
-Implementación de procesos end to end y mejora de procesos a diferentes niveles bajo la estructura y metodología APQC.
-Proyectos de consultoría para factibilidad de proyectos.

Con experiencia en aplicación de metodología Lean Six sigma y sus herramientas y metodologías de proyectos ágiles SCRUM

Experiencia trabajando en industrias como aviación, retail, logística, consultoría, financiera y gestión de recursos humanos, ejecutando para la mayoría de ellos una administración de proyectos multi país, teniendo equipos basados en diferentes países latinoamericanos y del caribe inglés, lo cual me permitió poder conocer más de 10 países y sus culturas y la oportunidad de entender los proyectos y procesos desde perspectivas diferentes.

Actualmente lidero proyectos enfocados a logística, procesos y experiencia al cliente, así como implementación de sistemas, por medio de la utilización de herramientas de mejora continua y gestión de proyectos para buscar los mejores resultados al menor costo posible, obteniendo optimizaciones e implementaciones efectivas de acuerdo a los requerimientos del negocio, así como experiencia en procesos financieros, logísticos, recursos humanos, comercial y experiencia al cliente.

De los diferentes roles que he ejercido así como de los diferentes proyectos que lidere, he aprendido que el valor de la comunicación y la alineación estratégica son pilares claves para el éxito de todo proyecto.
También, el valor de una correcta administración de recursos y gestión de proyectos de acuerdo a una metodología como la del PMI, que permite tener la certeza de incluir todos los elementos que son claves en la dirección de cualquier tipo de proyecto, como lo es la administración de costos, tiempos, recursos, calidad y satisfacción del cliente; todo esto, de la mano con la mejora continua y la identificación temprana de los riesgos.

Me defino como una persona comunicativa, positiva, pro activa, carismática con una alta capacidad de relacionarme, liderar y trabajar en equipo en diferentes ambientes, con una gran capacidad de aprendizaje y análisis, a quien le gusta trazarse retos y metas para alcanzarlos.

description:
I started out in digital media in 2006 as a Campaign Analyst as a part of SearchRev, a Palo Alto California based Online Advertising company. As a collective effort, we created online platforms, which are still in use in thousands of campaigns worldwide. I specialized in ROI target based optimization and conversion tracking. This was my first full-time job, and my passion for the field of modern advertising grew here.

SearchRev was then acquired by San Francisco based digital media giant AKQA and I was promoted to a Campaign Manager and ran performance based campaigns for companies like Shutterfly, Pandora, Verizon Wireless, HSBC, Ticketmaster while working from the El Salvador AKQA hub. At the AKQA El Salvador Hub I also led search, display, video and mobile campaigns for Coca-Cola LCBU Latin America from 2009 to 2011.

I was later on promoted to General Manager at the office and oversaw day to day management operations of the same office I developed. This included business financials and accounting, human resource management, direction, motivation and overall development and training of staff to ensure growth for the project.

I was then hired at White Shark Media to take the lead in the creation and direction of their search marketing efforts. Our main goal was the retention of our client base to ensure company profitability. With the aid of a well-trained team, we handle hundreds of clients ensuring that all processes were streamlined, coherent and up to par with client and market expectations.

After Developing Talent at my previous company and helping them to achieve a prestigious agency status, my entrepreneurial instinct kicked in, and with the help of our agency co-founders, we kick-started a Search Marketing Agency, Flame Tree Marketing. Flame Tree Marketing has grown to become a 50 person headcount agency, with numerous happy clients and high volume ad spend.

description:
Shaun is a passionate and seasoned technology consulting leader with almost 20 years of IT consulting experience. He loves solving client problems, delivering high quality deliverables and being a trusted advisor to his clients. On the business side he focuses on Digital Marketing Strategy, Web & Mobile Strategy, CRM & Customer Strategy. On the tech side he has spent much time dedicated to Program, Project, and Agile Management, Business/Technical Analysis, Vendor Assessments, Solution and Technical Architecture & Roadmapping, Business Process Design, Test Planning & Execution, Test Process and Tools, Training Development & Delivery, Agile Release Planning, Agile Execution (using Scrum and XP) and Agile Transformation and Coaching. He has worked across large and small clients in the Telecommunications, Auto, Finance, Hospitality, Retail, and Insurance industries including AT&T, Verizon Business, Cox Automotive, IHG, ADP, The Home Depot, and Airbnb.

Shaun’s career started at Accenture in 2001 where he focused on telecommunications and large system implementations. After Accenture, Shaun joined Slalom and spent almost a decade working to establish their reputation in the Atlanta market and became a Consultant Manager and Client Service Lead for several clients. Since Co-Founding ImagineX Consulting in 2015, Shaun has owned their technology practices including Adaptive Agile and Software Engineering & Cloud. He has grown the Atlanta office to be ImagineX’s National Delivery Center, and home to 40 consultants and growing rapidly. Shaun is currently involved in GA Tech’s StartUp eXchange, UGA’s Terry College Mentoring Program, and KSU’s Gold Circle Leaders in Entrepreneurship and focuses corporate sponsorship on Camp Horizon of Georgia. Shaun was a 2018 finalist for Atlanta Business Chronicle's Small Business Person of the Year. Shaun became CEO of ImagineX in January 2020.

In his spare time, Shaun loves to travel, spend time with his family, and attempt to maintain his 2 handicap on the golf course.

description:
Ed Wiley is a high-visibility senior executive with over 20 years of building, leading, and advising world-class machine learning, AI, and data science teams at companies at stages from startup to Fortune 50. An active member of the AI and data science communities, Ed regularly presents at national and international conferences and workshops and has been named a "Top Big Data Pro To Follow On Twitter" (@WileyEd; http://tinyurl.com/TopDataPros; >16k followers).

Key professional experiences include:
⇒ Built and led the first Data Science practice as Chief Data Scientist at Sears Holdings (NASDAQ: SHLD)
⇒ Built and led the first Big Data practice at Seagate Technology (NASDAQ: STX)
⇒ Author of forthcoming (Q1 2021) book "AI: From Buzzword to Business Function. A Leader's Playbook for Bringing AI, Machine Learning, and Data Science to your Business"
⇒ McKinsey-trained business strategist and executive consultant
⇒ Stanford-educated Ph.D. Statistician/Data Scientist

⇒ Track record of successful delivery of production, enterprise-scale data/analytics products

In his work as a data scientist and strategy specialist, Ed leverages rich experience in business strategy as well as superior quantitative/analytical and leadership/interpersonal skills. Across his professional experiences, he's established a proven record of generating and implementing creative ideas to bring about measurable change.

As Vice President of Data & Machine Learning at Nurx, Ed built and led a new team of machine learning engineers and mathematicians who pushed the envelope of AI technologies (e.g., machine learning; deep learning; Hadoop; Spark) to help Nurx reinvent healthcare delivery.

Contact Ed <ed@edwiley.com> to schedule time to talk about building data science teams, opportunities for improving business outcomes with AI & data science, or leading data science teams (especially for those without a data science background).

description:
What I know about you is that you are powerful. You are more powerful than you think you are, more powerful than you may be experiencing right now and even more powerful than you believe you can be. You are powerful!

It is my passion, purpose and joy to coach powerful women leaders when they have lost the connection to their innate power and are searching for how to reconnect so they can continue to make an impact in their career, be financially secure and have the time and energy to fully enjoy all of their life.

If you agree that this is you, then you know what it feels like to be moving through life powerfully. You’ve had promotions, accolades, financial success and more.

However, you recognize that your life has changed. Maybe you have ended up in a job that is financially secure but emotionally draining. Maybe you lost out on a big project or promotion to someone younger than you. You may even be one of the 56% of people over 50 who lose their jobs before they are ready to retire.

You may also be experiencing changes on a personal level such as a change in a close relationship, a big move, physical trauma, children leaving the nest or parents aging.

There is no question that all of these changes can lead to stress, frustration and self doubt.

What I know with absolute certainty is that you can reconnect to your power. You can have the life you desire. And, you can have the best career of your life after 40, 50, even 60 and beyond.

I know this because I have been exactly where you are now and not only did I discover how to re-connect to my power, for 15 years I have coached 100’s of women to do the same.

I’m excited and honored that you took the time to read through my ‘about’ page. If you recognize yourself on this page please reach out to me.
• Sign up for Morning Mindset and wake up each morning with a note of encouragement or an idea to start your day with enthusiasm: www.connecttoyourpower.com/morning-mindset/
• Pickup Tips on Overcoming Ageism: http://www.connecttoyourpower.com/podcasts/
• Sign up for a free consultation at: https://calendly.com/jeastbarr/powerful-at-any-age

IDEA es una empresa que fue fundada en los años 90, con el objetivo de brindar el servicio de distribución, almacenaje y logística en la región de Centroamérica, ofreciendo soluciones de control para optimizar la cadena de abastecimiento de nuestros clientes.

Con el pasar de los años IDEA fue creciendo y adaptándose a las nuevas necesidades que han ido surgiendo en el ámbito logístico, y de acorde a las obligaciones legales de cada región, permitiendo de esta manera innovar y presentar en el mercado logístico la mejor alternativa. description:
Nelson Albareda, a Cuban-American business executive and GRAMMY® & Latin GRAMMY® Award winning producer, has over 25 years of diverse experience across media, live entertainment, marketing, content, sports and real estate.

Albareda got an early start in business at the age of 14 in 1990, where he became passionate about business and entrepreneurship. He had a successful career as a young professional, quickly moving up the ranks across multiple companies and diverse industries, including in the advertising, spirits, entertainment and media sectors. Initially starting at RMM Records (Universal Music), and eventually ending up at Univision Radio where he was responsible for creating the company’s non-traditional revenue initiatives across the organization.

In 2002, Albareda saw an opportunity in the events, entertainment and marketing space, which is where he had early success as an entrepreneur. Most notably in 2005, Albareda established Eventus, which grew to serve and partner with a wide-range of marquee clients such as Sony Music, Univision Communications, New York Yankees, Kimberly-Clark, Walmart, McDonald’s, Keurig Dr Pepper, HBO, Walt Disney Entertainment, Sirius XM and Latin GRAMMY’s among many others. In 2013, Eventus had become the largest multicultural marketing company in the US, which is when Albareda sold the company to Advantage Solutions via a roll-up strategy led by private equity group Apax Partners.

In 2017, Albareda established Loud And Live, where he currently serves as CEO. The company has quickly grown to be a dominant player across its areas of focus, including music, entertainment, sports, content development and marketing.

In addition to his endeavors at Loud And Live, Nelson has a real-estate portfolio and management company focused on commercial and multi-family properties in South Florida.

Albareda also has a long history of serving his community. In 2010, he was appointed by the US Congress to serve as a Commissioner on the Federal Commission to provide a report to President Obama on the creation of the National Museum of the American Latino in Washington DC. He also currently serves as a Member of the Board of Directors on the US Cuba Democracy PAC and F.A.C.E (Facts About Cuban Exiles).
headline: President & CEO at Loud And Live

Cristina es de nacionalidad paraguaya, posee sólida experiencia en originación, estructuración y manejo de operaciones de préstamos para PYMES e instituciones financieras, habiendo liderado operaciones en Paraguay y Bolivia, principalmente, y en otros países latinoamericanos como El Salvador y Panamá. Antes de unirse a la CII, Cristina trabajó como Oficial de Banca Privada en el Banco Alemán Paraguayo S.A., como Administradora del Proyecto PRIME de USAID y como Gerente Comercial de una empresa privada paraguaya. Posee una especialización en Finanzas de la escuela de negocios INCAE, cursos aprobados del MBA y dos licenciaturas una en Contabilidad y otra en Administración Agraria. Ha recibido la medalla de honor al mérito ciudadano otorgada por la Municipalidad de Asunción, Paraguay, por su gran aporte a la cultura.

description:
Professional experienced in managing and coordinating human resources as well as business processes, and day-to-day operations. Strong problem solver with the ability to manage multiple tasks related to the human resource department. Experience in enhance leadership skills, efficient, and effective teams.

Before joining Startup Genome Arnobio led entrepreneurship data efforts at the Kauffman Foundation, a multi-billion dollar foundation focused on entrepreneurship and education. There he created some of the most widely used entrepreneurship indicators in the US -- the Kauffman Index for Growth and Main Street Entrepreneurship. These indicators, together with the long-running Kauffman Index of Startup Activity, have been called the “bible of entrepreneurship trends,” and have been used by senators, governors, city leaders, Fortune 500 companies, and the White House. He also led on the Kauffman Foundation side a multi-million dollar public-private partnership with the US Census Bureau to create the largest annual survey of entrepreneurs ever done.

Arnobio’s research and analysis have been featured widely in national and global media, including the New York Times, the Economist, the Wall Street Journal, and the BBC, among others. He is a frequent public speaker and has presented at South by Southwest, Facebook, the Federal Reserve Bank, and many others. Arnobio has advised, worked with, and presented to CEOs, founders, current and former government ministers, and top academics.

** Canadian Citizen currently leaving abroad.

Twelve years in Product and Innovation at Pearson US and UK, working in markets across the world, gave me a global perspective and an acute understanding of how innovation happens in large organisations.

I joined Reed Learning in 2014 to tackle professional development in an area where learning could be applied immediately in the real world. I led on product, strategy and innovation with ultimate responsibility for the long term vision of the company and delivery of the learning experience.

In 2016 I founded The Honeycomb Works, a development partner for organisations who need to drive behavioural change for business transformation. It uses a unique framework and visual tool to organise and deliver diagnostics, coaching, workshops and digital support in learning.

My strengths lie in viewing the market holistically and developing solutions iteratively, in close collaboration with clients and learnings. I have experience delivering executive workshops and speak regularly on learning and innovation.

description:
Caroline has been Director of Behavioural Science & Research at The Honeycomb Works, since its inception in 2016. Leading the research team in pursuit of THCW's goal of creating organisational cultures that support people to belong and invent, through meaningful research to build scalable technology.

She is passionate about using an evidence based, agile approach to researching and developing genuinely inclusive workplaces. Taking a pragmatic approach, driven by a human centred focus on creating change for individuals first, then organisations.

In support of her commitment to practical, applicable research Caroline leads on independent research and regularly speaks at industry events.

She is also the VP of Membership Engagement & Experience for PWN Barcelona, a global community that exists to advance gender balanced leadership.

Caroline lives in the mountains just outside Barcelona, where she moved from London in 2019, loves travelling (when allowed), keeps chickens and is working on her Spanish.

description:
Who Am I...

For over 20 years, I have been a part of high profile, technology engagements while operating as an independent consultant, enabling business transformation through the integration of next generation, technically enabled solutions. I've been involved in projects that have represented pioneering solutions within Telemedicine and IoT.

My current work, as a technology thought leader, focuses around cloud-enabled, hyper scalable solutions, where I lead cross-functional project teams to solve business problems and create opportunities.

Over the years while working as a Lead Consultant for various Fortune 500 companies, not only my passion for technology has grown, but also my vision for the future of technology.

Skills & Passions…

Collaboration, Innovation, and Global Impact. I love to immerse in relevant technologies that bring about rapid and disruptive change. I give preference to those companies who have a noble mission statement.

I'm OK with highly difficult assignments.. Challenges with technology are not an if, but a when, and having the right mindset around meeting adversity allows for faster, more creative solution responses. Success is built on the back of failure because it is not about falling down but how you get back up.

Public cloud has opened up the possibility to innovate and respond faster than ever before. There are multiple open-sourced and defined technologies such as 5G, Blockchain, AI frameworks (TensorFlow, Pytorch), established AI models with trained data, that allow for fascinating creations that will rapidly evolve how we interface with the world.

Where Am I Going…

I'm particularly interested in how healthcare and smart cities will embrace all the technologies that I have touched upon, as well as new developments.
There is much opportunity given the connectivity of the 21st century to save many institutions their most valued asset, TIME.

It is my belief, and personal goal that we have the capability, through technology... to enable smart cities, be more productive with full self-driving cars, diagnose medical conditions faster, develop better drugs, create better understanding of our genetics to mitigate life threatening conditions, and expand our ability to engage in life in a deeper, more meaningful and productive way.

✅ Through collaborative, innovative, and technology driven solutions, we can change the world!

✅ If a digitally enabled future fascinates you, feel free to reach out to me via Linkedin email or DM.

✅ Let's make the future happen now

description:
Hello there,

Thank you for stopping by and check out my profile, let me walk you through by who I am as a person and as professional.

WHO AM I? 👋
I'm a passionate, creative, and eager HR Professional with 8+ years of experience working with HR management's full life cycle, from recruitment and talent acquisition, payroll, employee relations and labor relations, compensations, and benefits to Performance Management.

My colleagues think I am a joker, and believe me, I'm a funny guy who likes to make people laugh at work and have fun, but seriously, I'm also the one who gets things done.

I enjoy working with and for people, and this is part of my management style:

1. As a colleague, I'm a team player, negotiator, and excellent communicator, and I'm proactive and creative in finding solutions for problems.
2. As a leader, I'm a coach and foster, and I like to teach and share knowledge with my team if they have a problem, so have I. We share responsibility, and I make sure to develop a safe.net environment, where they can feel free to share fears and difficulties.
3. With my leaders, I'm resilient and committed person, I take ownership of every project and tasks, and when I fail, I take responsibility to improve next time.
4. As a person, I'm the one who tells jokes, but I'm also the one who takes work seriously. In the past, people tend to think I was not a good employee, "funny to be serious, they said". And guess what?, here I am thriving organizing from HR.

WHAT DO I DO, AND HOW DO I DO IT?
1. I help organizations, companies, leaders and individual contributor, designing and implementing strategies to strengthen and improve the work culture, communications process, and teamwork, which aim to have a high impact on the business results, always looking for trends and new ways to implement innovation as part of my job.
2. I keep myself up to date with knowledge so that I can come up with fresh ideas and strategies on Performance Management, Employee's Experience and relations, Recruitment, Compensations.

RECRUITMENT AND TALENT ACQUISITION
I help companies with sourcing and hiring the best talented IT and Non-IT profiles, from Software Developers, including Frontend and Backend technologies, (React, Angular, VueJS, JavaScript, PHP, Laravel, Java, .NET among others) and Mobile technologies (iOS, Android, Xamarin).

HOW DO I DO THIS?
1. I use various sourcing methods, including LinkedIn.
2. I talk about tech and Non-Tech Jargon.
3. I speak with people, not with robots, so we have a good time chatting with candidates.
4. I´m, a good negotiator.
